      <h3>How it began, from the Santrepreneur who started this whole thing</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="story-left col-5">
        <p>In 2011, I quit my job to start a social enterprise. I took a leap and quickly fell on my face. And it hurt. There was a loss of identity, repeated failures and insecurities. I felt damaged. To learn more about social enterprises and more about myself, I moved to India.
        Life in India challenged my beliefs, particularly around health and the environment. I started listening to my body, stopped watching calories, kicked a coffee habit, meditated daily, eliminated unnecessary consumption, replaced feelings of anger and guilt with love, compassion and gratitude and researched becoming Vegan. The vegan component led me to Garcinia indica. 
        It hasn’t been easy, yet I’m grateful for the experience.  I can’t imagine doing anything other than promoting balance, health, the environment, love, gratitude, and compassion.  There the things I value. And it feels good when your actions match your values.
        Hugs, Kim
        </p>
